{"title":"Happy Bicycle Day!","link":"https://theradavist.com/happy-bicycle-day/","date":1681931633000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1537\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/04/1992-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/04/1992-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/04/1992-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,615&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/04/1992-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1201&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/04/1992-scaled.jpg?resize=768,461&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/04/1992-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1081&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/04/1992-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,802&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/04/1992-scaled.jpg?resize=700,420&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/04/1992-scaled.jpg?resize=600,360&amp;quality=75 600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/04/1992-scaled.jpg?resize=1200,720&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/04/1992-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,922&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/04/1992-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1230&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.brianblomerth.com/\">Brian Blomerth’s</a> graphic novel <em>Bicycle Day</em> tells the story of the first LSD trip: a psychedelic ride made in 1943 by Swiss chemist Albert Hofmann as he sampled the first-ever LSD. Each year, on April 19th, the world celebrates Bicycle Day as an homage to Hofmann’s chemical mixture that forever changed the world of psychedelics.</p>\n<p>If you’d like to see an in-depth look at Blomerth’s book, check out this article at <a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/gallery/2019/aug/06/graphic-history-first-lsd-trip-brain-blomerth-bicycle-day-in-pictures\" target=\"_blank\">The Guardian</a>.</p>\n<p><em>BRB, we’re going on a ride…</em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/happy-bicycle-day/\">Happy Bicycle Day!</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"5ac61fb371a4f9f8837ce35128a0ac8163ff70f5fde3e69a2106c00e8ade4761","category":"Cycling"}